 | accessdate = 2007-11-21
}}</ref> Injection in saline is normally conducted intramuscularly (IM) in [[skeletal muscle]], or [[dermis|intradermally]] (ID), with DNA being delivered to the extracellular spaces. This can be assisted by [[electroporation]];<ref name=Widera2000>{{cite journal
 | author = Widera, G.
 | coauthors = Austin, M.; Rabussay, D.; Goldbeck, C.; Barnett, S.W.; Chen, M.; Leung, L.; Otten, G.R.; Thudium, K.; Selby, M.J.; Others,
